If South Africa’s credit rating is downgraded again there is a risk of a “sudden stop” in non-residents’ appetite for local bonds, the central bank said on Thursday. “Domestic bonds may still remain attractive as they are classified as high-yielding securities,” the bank said in its latest financial stability review. “However, from the financial stability perspective, there is a risk of a sudden stop in non-residents’ appetite for local bonds if South Africa were to be downgraded.” 